d 'POISSARK': module to perform Poisson regression with integer-valued autoregressive-corrected standard errors
d
d     poissark fits Poisson regression models for count time series
d with autoregressive errors of order k. Regression coefficients
d are estimated by Poisson maximum likelihood; the AR thinning
d parameters rho_1,...,rho_k are estimated by conditional least
d squares (CLS) applied to the integer-valued autoregressive
d (INAR(p)) model of Du and Li (1991), which extends the INAR(1)
d model of McKenzie (1985) and Al-Osh and Alzaid (1987) to
d arbitrary order using independent binomial thinning at each lag.
d Standard errors for the regression coefficients are corrected via
d an INAR-corrected sandwich estimator that accounts for the
d estimated autocorrelation structure (Klimko and Nelson 1978).
d Only positive autocorrelation is supported (rho_j >= 0), which is
d a fundamental constraint of the binomial thinning mechanism. 
d
d KW: Poisson regression
d KW: autoregressive errors
d KW: conditional least squares
d KW: integer-valued autoregressive model
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260611
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
f poissark.ado
f poissark_p.ado
f poissark.sthlp
f poissark_example.dta
